cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Simply Put in your work, please cite it as below."
title: "Simply Put: a plain-language readability rig with a deterministic gate and dual-model judge"
abstract: >-
  Plainish rewrites text to plain language through an agentic pipeline gated
  by a public, reproducible Flesch-Kincaid score, with an opt-in dual-model
  LLM judge for meaning-preservation and an Oban batch + LiveView dashboard
  for before/after reading-level tracking.
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Brittany Reese
    family-names: Markides
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6242-0842"
version: 0.1.0
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/brittanyreese/simply-put"
url: "https://github.com/brittanyreese/simply-put"
keywords:
  - elixir
  - phoenix
  - llm
  - readability
  - flesch-kincaid
  - agentic-pipeline
  - oban
  - liveview
